"The Interstellar Explorer and the Digital Web
Drifting through the endless void between stars, I have witnessed nebulae bloom like cosmic flowers, planets whisper secrets in the gravity of their orbits, and black holes devour light itself. But nothing—nothing—has been as perplexing as the internet. As humanity’s first lone interstellar explorer, I left Earth decades ago to chart the unknown. Yet, even from the depths of deep space, I still receive transmissions from the homeworld. Of all the signals that reach my ship, none are as chaotic, vibrant, and utterly indecipherable as the vast digital landscape humans call the internet. It is a universe unto itself, a tangled web of knowledge"


